 This role provides the opportunity to inspire and engage with Quality and Supply Chain leaders as we globally accelerate Enterprise Intelligent Automation Initative ambition. Our world class Quality & Compliance team is leveraging the cutting-edge technologies of Robotic Process Automation, Virtual Agents, Machine Learning, AI and others, to modernize internal business functions thru data enabled decision-making processes, ultimately increasing effectiveness while changing experience and adding value for our customers. 
 This role will be deeply connected to our global Q&C teams, including Strategy & Innovation, Digital &Data Science while working in close collaboration with JJTechnology and under Enterprise IA Council guidance. We are looking for a multi-disciplinary, Quality savvy business leader who can help us to further develop, execute, and drive the Intelligent Automation program within JnJ Q&C. This leader should have passion for improving business processes end-to-end in achieving the most optimal business and customer experience. This is a high visibility role within our Enterprise Q&C team. The leader in this role will have direct contact with various executives across our Sectors and geographies. 
 About J&J‚Äôs Supply Chain Intelligent Automation Focus Area 
As part of J&J‚Äôs global supply chain network the Intelligent Automation initiative is a key focus area in our innovation journey as we continue to be world-class. The scope will span; providing strategic and tactical direction to the PMO, on the top priorities for Intelligent Automation, In Collaboration with Quality and supply chain leaders identifying needs across business and functions where IA can advance business agenda, co-developing workforce strategies and evangelising the value across JnJ. Linkage to the customer and adding value to the various tounchpoints of the end-to-end Q&C and supply chain is imperative for success in this role. 
 Role and Responsibilities 
The Senior Director, Intelligent Automation Application Q&C, will focus on understanding opportunities across Sectors and on determining the top areas of focus where data and insights can drive process automation . This must include reimaging and automating Q&C processes end-to-end within the Q&C and supply chain, to drive agility, reliability and efficiencies. Building a collaborative working relationship will be key to the success. 
This role will be reporting to the Vice President,Emerging technologies & solution Q&C. 
 Strategy and Execution Leadership 
 Responsible and accountable for directing PMO in developing portfolio management, necessary engagement and operating model across all sectors and Q&C functions to enable program objectives Enables segment led Intelligent Automation priorities Drives risk identification, management, and mitigation to enable value realization. In collaboration with Enterprise Council and functions, assures development and attainment of program objectives Develops and implements standardized program reporting and analytics Effectively engages and communicates with executive sponsors and key stakeholders, developing a regular cadence of communications Thought leadership & embedded in external eco-sytems to gain insights in industry trends related to IA Technologies and activate these & deploy business applications in J&J Q&C to drive SC competiveness enabling growth and enhanced value for customers. 
Communication 
 Drive clear communications to all stakeholders on goals, timing, processes, and metrics for success. 
 
